Sentencas: Thin films of scandia-stabilized zirconia (ScSZ) for a solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) electrolyte were prepared using electron beam vapor deposition.
Titulo: Preparation of Scandia-Stabilized Zirconia Electrolyte Thin Films for Intermediate Temperature-Solid Oxide Fuel Cells by Electron Beam Vapor Deposition

Sentencas: The effects of annealing temperature, substrate temperature, and e-beam gun power on the structure and surface morphology of the thin films were examined.
Titulo: Preparation of Scandia-Stabilized Zirconia Electrolyte Thin Films for Intermediate Temperature-Solid Oxide Fuel Cells by Electron Beam Vapor Deposition

Sentencas: It was found that the ScSZ thin film samples annealed at approximately 1000 degrees C consisted of a single cubic phase.
Titulo: Preparation of Scandia-Stabilized Zirconia Electrolyte Thin Films for Intermediate Temperature-Solid Oxide Fuel Cells by Electron Beam Vapor Deposition

Sentencas: The crystal orientation of the ScSZ films increased with substrate temperature and with e-beam gun power.
Titulo: Preparation of Scandia-Stabilized Zirconia Electrolyte Thin Films for Intermediate Temperature-Solid Oxide Fuel Cells by Electron Beam Vapor Deposition

Sentencas: A good adhesion to the substrate and a columnar structure were observed from the fractured cross-sectional view of the ScSZ films on a NiO-YSZ anode substrate.
Titulo: Preparation of Scandia-Stabilized Zirconia Electrolyte Thin Films for Intermediate Temperature-Solid Oxide Fuel Cells by Electron Beam Vapor Deposition

Sentencas: The ionic conductivity of the ScSZ film with 2.5 mu m thickness was observed to be 9.46 x 10(-3) Scm(-1)
Titulo: Preparation of Scandia-Stabilized Zirconia Electrolyte Thin Films for Intermediate Temperature-Solid Oxide Fuel Cells by Electron Beam Vapor Deposition

Sentencas: at 700 degrees C with the conduction activation energy of 0.82 eV.
Titulo: Preparation of Scandia-Stabilized Zirconia Electrolyte Thin Films for Intermediate Temperature-Solid Oxide Fuel Cells by Electron Beam Vapor Deposition

Sentencas: The results in this study showed that the crystallite size of the ScSZ thin films and thus the electrochemical properties can be improved by optimizing e-beam deposition conditions and annealing temperature.
Titulo: Preparation of Scandia-Stabilized Zirconia Electrolyte Thin Films for Intermediate Temperature-Solid Oxide Fuel Cells by Electron Beam Vapor Deposition
